Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:18.36,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.41,0:01:46.39,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,270)}Ep. 05 - After the Rain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.52,0:02:05.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous, Lucy-May!\NPlease come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.16,0:02:25.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In her animal-loving daze, Lucy-May was approaching a pack of sea lions,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.64,0:02:28.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,unable to hear me begging her to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.60,0:02:47.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.78,0:03:00.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Keep calm\Nand I won't do anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.08,0:03:03.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because I know you won't do anything to me either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.82,0:03:18.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.78,0:03:21.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Flee! Flee that place, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.88,0:04:11.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.31,0:04:14.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They all hid in the sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:22.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking standing idly,\Nsurrounded by a pack of sea lions?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.12,0:04:25.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about how sea lions\Nare absolutely cute when you look closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.49,0:04:27.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Were you really not one bit scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:29.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:30.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.56,0:04:36.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I though they could eat you any moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.15,0:04:37.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.94,0:04:41.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! It sure is raining hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:43.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's find a shelter somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:45.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Under those rocks should do. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.12,0:04:50.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, the sea lions\Nhate thunderstorms just as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:04.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There, we're home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:09.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! You're not as wet as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:11.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.96,0:05:14.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We took shelter at Mrs. Jamling's text.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.70,0:05:17.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it seemed like it won't stop any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:20.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Jamling finally return?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.14,0:05:21.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.40,0:05:25.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I just heard that he left for Adelaide yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.55,0:05:28.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Also that he wasn't planning to stay there overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.48,0:05:31.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Jamling seems to grow really worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:35.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's also blowing hard.\NThis rain really {\i1}is{\i0} here to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.50,0:05:41.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your dad and Ben are probably\Nexploring Adelaide sodden wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.80,0:05:48.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The wind picked up, Mr. Jamling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:49.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'd better get home sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.84,0:05:52.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if we head out now,\Nwe'll get soaked at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.86,0:05:55.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My wife is probably pulling her hair out...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.38,0:05:59.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not so far from the tents now.\NBut with that leg...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.27,0:06:01.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure there is no fracture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:04.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just a small sprain,\Nnot something that'd prevent me from walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.57,0:06:09.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When we get back to the tents,\Nwe should show you to a physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.51,0:06:12.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Physician?\NI thought there are no physicians around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.94,0:06:15.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. There are none ashore,\Nbut not on the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.33,0:06:20.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the naval surgeon.\NThat man who never gets sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.29,0:06:22.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's the only physician we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.22,0:06:26.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple, we should head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:29.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind getting sodden wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.58,0:06:33.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to trouble you, but could you\Nfind a branch for me to use as a walking stick?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.61,0:06:37.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You want to return on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.10,0:06:38.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.26,0:06:45.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.23,0:06:49.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You saved my life, truly,\Nby carrying me all the way to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.53,0:06:52.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have to take over from here on somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.17,0:06:53.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If I had a walking stick, I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.63,0:06:56.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Jamling, we'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.29,0:06:59.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll get wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.40,0:07:04.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here. Please get on my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:13.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:23.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This rain isn't gonna stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.20,0:07:24.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.76,0:07:26.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's just the feeling I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.67,0:07:29.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think it'll be stopping soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.00,0:07:30.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.14,0:07:31.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's just the feeling I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.82,0:07:33.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't copy after me, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:35.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that's how I really feel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.56,0:07:38.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You could wait all day,\Nbut the sea lions won't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.58,0:07:42.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting soaked here anyhow.\NLet's head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.83,0:07:45.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. Mom is probably worried too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.60,0:07:46.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.52,0:07:51.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me and mom had our share of worrying\Nwhen dad didn't return from Adelaide last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.88,0:07:54.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At a time like this, the sooner we return - the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.69,0:08:07.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, don't fall behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:11.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, do you remember where you tossed shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.19,0:08:12.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:14.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't sound terribly confident to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.13,0:08:17.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm not confident.\NYou'll help us look for it, won't you, Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.55,0:08:18.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I gotta!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.00,0:08:24.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.89,0:08:25.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.93,0:08:28.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Will your tent be able to weather this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:29.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.10,0:08:34.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If the wind gets any stronger,\Nthere will probably be some flying tents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.44,0:08:37.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to think that our tent can handle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.34,0:08:39.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, mine is not at risk either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.81,0:08:42.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's because you're a carpenter,\Naren't you, Mr. Jamling?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:46.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But my dad is a farmer,\Nand thanks to that he's also very dexterous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:48.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why our tent is stretched tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.11,0:08:49.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I helped set it up too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.34,0:08:52.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.04,0:08:56.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope Billy makes just as helpful\Nan assistant to me when he's your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.05,0:09:00.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Billy is ten, right?\NHe's the same age as our Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.37,0:09:01.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If so, you can't blame him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.13,0:09:05.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For example, Kate is good-for-nothing, compared to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.38,0:09:09.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Caught a cold already?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:12.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a cold,\Nsimply something in my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.94,0:09:18.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Clara finally got better,\Nmy another big sister comes down ill!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.51,0:09:20.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not ill, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:21.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.82,0:09:26.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's it behind that rock?\NThe place where you tossed your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.52,0:09:28.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think so too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.32,0:09:35.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's here, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.78,0:09:37.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's here, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.77,0:09:42.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This way, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.73,0:09:46.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd. They should totally be around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.87,0:09:50.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just stare idly! Help me look for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.77,0:09:53.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eck!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.93,0:09:55.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.11,0:09:56.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I stepped on...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.26,0:09:57.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,On what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:10:00.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know yet.\NBut it's so slimy to the touch...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.32,0:10:01.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can you move your foot away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.96,0:10:03.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I suppose.
Comment: 0,0:10:03.66,0:10:04.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.75,0:10:09.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.19,0:10:14.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It went that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:15.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.74,0:10:17.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.46,0:10:19.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:22.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.02,0:10:25.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.58,0:10:28.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you seen snakes like that?\NIt has proper legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.52,0:10:29.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's a lizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:31.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose. Must be a lizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:32.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it has two heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.28,0:10:33.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.30,0:10:37.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What a curious fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.40,0:10:44.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it comes out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.14,0:10:47.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna check if it really has two heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.49,0:10:49.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it doesn't bite...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.09,0:10:51.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did it bite you, Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.53,0:10:53.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.94,0:10:57.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,See? Didn't bite even after being stepped on.\NIt's gotta be alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.43,0:11:02.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I should've heeded to mom's advice, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.64,0:11:04.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.09,0:11:06.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There are dangerous insects in the grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.13,0:11:09.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,so she told me to wear shoes at all times,\Nlest I'll get stung.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:11.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The head must be on the side that it walked with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:13.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This one certainly was no insect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.60,0:11:16.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It looked like a lizard, albeit an odd-shaped one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:20.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It being a lizard only makes matters worse!\NI'm not taking my shoes off ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:24.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Start looking for my shoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.29,0:11:27.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not setting a bare foot in that grass again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:29.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.27,0:11:32.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your shoes were right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.23,0:11:34.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You found them in a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:38.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure I tossed them that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:40.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone must've brought them here, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:42.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right! That's gotta be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:44.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But who would do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.32,0:11:47.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No reason any of the immigrants would come to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.99,0:11:50.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But who'd ever be interested\Nin fooling around with some shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.36,0:11:53.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.33,0:11:56.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I figured it out!\NI know who fooled around with the shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:11:57.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.60,0:11:58.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.99,0:12:02.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hiding in the shadow from the rock\Nto the side behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.14,0:12:09.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be him, who...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:11.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, gotta be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:13.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The kid that owns that cute baby bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:19.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I got some questions.\NLike where does one find an animal like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.44,0:12:25.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I've got something I want to ask you.\NWill you please tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.09,0:12:27.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That cute animal you're keeping...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.83,0:12:37.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he run off?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.79,0:12:39.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He probably thinks we're scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.84,0:12:43.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.06,0:12:47.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They probably think all the white people\Nwho arrived to this land are scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.87,0:13:50.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really? So you didn't make it to Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.02,0:13:53.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we judged that we should carry\Ninjured Mr. Jamling home first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:56.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly! You two did a great thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.60,0:14:00.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When we just got there,\NMrs. Jamling couldn't stop thanking dad in tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:02.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:06.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hurried to row into the open sea\Nto bring the doctor from the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.66,0:14:11.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When it's raining and blowing so hard,\Nrowing the boat all the way to the ship must be hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.49,0:14:13.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did he go there alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.32,0:14:14.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.40,0:15:03.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see the ship that brought us here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.21,0:15:05.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think it sailed back to England already?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:08.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was supposed to stay anchored\Nat this bay for three or four days more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.32,0:15:14.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. That ship still has\Nour prefabricated home on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.29,0:15:18.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably still anchored in the usual place,\Nbut we can't see it for the haze.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.65,0:15:21.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? What could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.13,0:15:25.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like a boat. Someone's riding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.13,0:15:27.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. Three people are riding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.66,0:15:35.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd wanna ride such a small boat\Namidst such high waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:36.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Totally not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.93,0:15:41.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, the waves are rocking it so hard.\NI wouldn't wanna ride it either at a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.83,0:15:43.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those must be very courageous people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.11,0:15:46.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Isn't it your very own dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.68,0:15:48.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There, the one who looks this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.59,0:15:51.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be! Our dad is in Adelaide today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.78,0:15:53.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose. Just someone alike, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.76,0:15:55.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's dad for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.73,0:16:03.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's waving to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:05.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then it must certainly be someone we know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:08.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, your dad's brother or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.51,0:16:10.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's gotta be dad himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.02,0:16:12.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's dad. No two ways about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.76,0:16:14.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.74,0:16:16.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.01,0:16:17.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.89,0:16:20.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.76,0:16:26.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.77,0:16:38.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.78,0:16:54.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this way, Doctor.\NJump on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.28,0:16:56.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right... I'm... now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.22,0:16:57.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.22,0:17:02.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Get yourself together, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.40,0:17:06.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I can't take it. I can't take it anymore,\Nnow I'm both booze-drunk and seasick-drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.31,0:17:13.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,W-What's that? Now even the earth is shaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.14,0:17:15.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, can't take it. I can't take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.49,0:17:21.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You guys. Why are you playing on the shore\Nduring such a terrible weather?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.83,0:17:27.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, dad! Did you ride this boat\Nall the way from Adelaide?{/came from ... on the ship
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.75,0:17:29.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.64,0:17:31.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, that hurt like hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.53,0:17:34.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see... How about here? Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.78,0:17:36.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.38,0:17:38.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean the bone is broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.10,0:17:43.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Seems to me like the bone is intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.71,0:17:46.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You'll be fine. It'll heal up in a week or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.80,0:17:49.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll need to keep it chilled with some cold water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.55,0:17:56.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, in two or three days,\Nwe'll need to move to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.74,0:18:00.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?\NDo you have a wagon or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.48,0:18:01.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.69,0:18:03.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Will you go there on foot?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:05.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hired an oxcart for our things. As for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.81,0:18:08.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't walk.\NForget about those "two or three days."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.88,0:18:11.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about it while you still have a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.34,0:18:15.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But there's plenty of work for me in Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.51,0:18:17.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Doctor! I'm a carpenter,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.93,0:18:22.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,and they're erecting a whole new city over there.\NCarpenters are in mad demand...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:23.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One week!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.43,0:18:27.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if possible,\Nten days of rest would be even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.16,0:18:31.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And remember, it's not just for the good of your leg,\Nbut for your own good as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:33.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ten days...
Comment: 0,0:18:33.93,0:18:35.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.12,0:18:38.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Change the compress frequently enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.28,0:18:38.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:40.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll have my leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.99,0:18:43.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:48.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, the sailor that rowed the boat for us\Nis waiting on the shore, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.04,0:18:51.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I think John went to my tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.24,0:18:52.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.29,0:18:55.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's because John is on good terms with my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.26,0:18:58.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I see. Right, right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:00.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple, I'm grateful for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.68,0:19:05.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,While you're here, there was something\NI wanted to talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.94,0:19:17.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Doctor. I'm sorry for making you wait.\NThis way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.74,0:19:20.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't happen to have any whiskey?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.30,0:19:21.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but not much of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:23.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could you treat me to just a cup?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.78,0:19:25.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.09,0:19:29.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If the weather is that hellish,\NI need it simply to endure another trip on a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.90,0:19:31.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like it stopped raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.80,0:19:36.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But this wind is still raging!\NI'm seriously worried about going back on a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:18.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon, Mr. Pettywell.
Comment: 0,0:20:20.40,0:20:21.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:25.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.90,0:20:41.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The hell! The damnation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.11,0:20:44.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Darling. What are saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.49,0:20:49.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.13,0:21:00.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to ferry that boozed Doctor\Nback to the ship soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:02.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't think I'd get to see you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.62,0:21:03.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Neither did I.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.53,0:21:04.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.24,0:21:06.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.68,0:21:08.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Welcome back, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.64,0:21:09.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.85,0:21:12.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, you're done with the checkup already?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.38,0:21:15.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A date inside an empty barrel?\NWell, ain't that romantic?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.73,0:21:17.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,W-We're just taking a shelter from the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.71,0:21:22.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No-no, it's no use hiding it.\NSomeone here just told me about what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.44,0:21:23.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.49,0:21:26.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But what a pity - in less than a week,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.91,0:21:29.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,you two will have to part for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.43,0:21:31.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.83,0:21:36.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if there'd be oceans between us,\Nour hearts will always stay together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.50,0:21:40.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, oh my. Now you even got me envious!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.08,0:21:43.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, we don't have much...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:45.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.43,0:21:57.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, John, we're leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.64,0:22:15.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow I'm going to Adelaide for sure
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.25,0:22:18.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,to find a place where we'll assemble\Nthe prefabricated home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.25,0:22:22.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is fed up with this cramped tent, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.73,0:22:31.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I ended up tending to Mr. Jamling\Nall day long instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.55,0:22:35.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Jamling also offered me something\Nas a token of his gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.08,0:22:40.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thing is, there are barely any horses or oxen\Nfit for transporting luggage in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.40,0:22:45.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, Mr. Jamling scouted a fantastic ox\Nand signed a contract with its owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.49,0:22:48.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But now he won't be able to walk\Non the day they settled on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.25,0:22:51.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So he passed to me his right to use that oxcart.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.74,0:22:54.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll be able to transport\Nall our belongings in one run?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.87,0:22:55.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.34,0:23:00.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even the big sofa I got from Mary\Nthat's still on the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.21,0:23:03.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly! According to Mr. Jamling,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.09,0:23:07.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,the transportation of big items is currently\Nthe one most difficult task around these places.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.43,0:23:11.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really, I'm so glad, honey!
Comment: 0,0:23:12.90,0:23:13.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.34,0:23:17.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That makes getting the land our only remaining concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.64,0:23:22.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By night, the rain had stopped.\NThe wind had settled down too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.92,0:23:27.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I'd be way happier,\Nsleeping in a proper house in the city of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.02,0:23:30.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But tonight, I wouldn't trade\Nthis barrel house for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.72,0:23:35.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think, Lucy-May might also\Nfeel this way about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.31,0:24:07.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and Ben went to Adelaide again\Nto look for a good plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.55,0:24:10.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But they couldn't obtain\Nneither the land, nor the oxcart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.65,0:24:14.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"A City Called Adelaide".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.51,0:24:15.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
